# Deep Chat styling

The bear chat UI uses the [Deep Chat](https://deepchat.dev) web component (`<deep-chat>`).

## Styling reference

Full docs: <https://deepchat.dev/docs/styles/>

Design examples (including "full width input"): <https://deepchat.dev/examples/design/>

## Key properties used in `bear_chat.html`

| JS property | What it controls |
|---|---|
| `style` / `chatStyle` | Host element (outer container) |
| `messageStyles` | Per-role bubble colours, alignment (`outerContainer.justifyContent`), padding |
| `textInput` | Input box styling, placeholder, character limit |
| `submitButtonStyles` | Send/loading/stop/disabled button states |
| `inputAreaStyle` | Bottom bar wrapping input + buttons |
| `auxiliaryStyle` | Raw CSS injected into Shadow DOM (scrollbar, internal overrides) |
| `avatars` | Avatar images/visibility per role |
| `names` | Name labels per role (text, colour, font) |

## Conventions

- All colour values are read at init from CSS custom properties (`--page-color`, `--text-color`, etc.) via `getComputedStyle`, not hard-coded.
- No rounded corners (`borderRadius: '0'`) per the Den design system.
- User bubbles: right-aligned, page-colour background with thin border.
- AI bubbles: left-aligned, surface-colour background.
- Input uses the "full width input" pattern: `border: 'unset'`, `borderTop` separator, `width: '100%'`.
